gurmukhi: AnMq CqRI Awn CY durMq rwj mY kro ] su ko iqhU jhwn mY smwj jaun qy tro ]156]
transliteration: Anant Chhatriaan Chhai Durant Raaj Maidaro|| Su Ko Tihoo Jahaan Mai Samaaj Jaoun Tedaro||156||
translation: “I am ruling after killing innumerable Kshatriyas; I am that one from whom the beings of all the three worlds run far away.156.

gurmukhi: AnMg rMg rMg ky surMg bwj mY hry ] bsyK rwjsÍie jg bwj myD mY kry ]
transliteration: Anan Ran Ran Ke Suran Baaj Mai Dare|| Basekh Raajsooe Jag Baaj Medh Mai Dare||
translation: “I have abducted many multi-coloured horses and have performed special Rajsu and Ashvamedha Yajnas;

gurmukhi: n BUm AYs ko rhI n j`g KMB jwinXY ] jgqR krx kwrx kru duqIX moih mwinXY ]157]
transliteration: Na Bhoom Ais Ko Rahina Jagg Khanbh Jaaniyai|| Jagtra Karan Kaaran Kar(u) Douteeya Moh(i) Maaniyai||157||
translation: “You may agree with me that any place or sacrificial column is not unacquainted with me; you may accept me as the second Lord of the world.157.

gurmukhi: su A`qR C`qR jy Dry su C`qR sUr syvhI ] AdMf KMf KMf ky sudMf moih dyvhI ]
transliteration: Su Attar Chhattra Je Ddare Su Chhattra Soor Sev-hee|| Adand Khanndkhanndke Sudand Moh(i) Dev-hee||
translation: “All the warriors who hold the arms and weapons are my servants; I have chopped into bits the unpunishable individuals and many of them are paying tributes to me;

gurmukhi: su AYs Aaur kOn hY pRqwpvwn jwnIAY ] qiRlok Awj ky ibKY joigMdR moih mwnIAY ]158]
transliteration: Su Ais Aur Kaoun Hai Prataapvaan Jaaneeai|| Trilok Aaj Ke Bikhai Jogindra Moh(i) Maaneeai||158||
translation: “None is considered glorious like me and O great Yogi ! consider me as the chief Administrator in all the three worlds.”158.

gurmukhi: khw BXo jo sB hI jg jIq su logn ko bhu qRws idKwXo ] Aaur khw ju pY dys ibdysn mwih Bly gj gwih bDwXo ]
transliteration: Kahaa Bhayo Jo Sabh Hijag Jeet Su Logad Ko Bahu Traas Dikhaayo|| Aur Kahaa Ji Pai Des Bidesan Maah(i) Bhale Gad Gadh(i) Badhaayo||
translation: “What then, if you have conquered and terrorized the whole world; what then, if you have got all the countries far and near crushed under the feet of your elephants;

gurmukhi: jo mn jIqq hY sB dys vhY qumrY niRp hwiQ n AwXo ] lwj geI kCu kwj srXo nhI lok gXo prlok n pwXo ]159]
transliteration: Jo Man Jeetat Hai Sabh Des Vahai Toumrai Nrip Haath(i) Na Aayo|| Laaj Gadkachh(u) Kaaj Daryo Nahilok Gado Parlok Na Paayo||159||
translation: “You have not got hat mind, which conquers all the countries all the countries; you have felt shyful before it several times and in this way, you have not only lost this world, but also the next world.159.

gurmukhi: BUm ko kaun gumwn hY BUpq so nhI kwhU ky sMg clY hY ] hY ClvMq bfI bsuDw Xih kwhU kI hY nh kwhU huAY hY ]
transliteration: Bhoom Ko Kaoun Goumaan Hai Bhoopat So Nahikaahoo Ke San Chalai Hai|| Hai Chhalvant Badi Basudhaa Yah(i) Kaahoo Kihai Nah Kaahoo Huai Hai||
translation: “O king! Why to be egoistic for the land, which does not accompany anyone on death; this earth is a great deceiver, it has not become one’s own uptil today, nor it will become anyone’s own;

gurmukhi: Baun BMBwr sBY br nwhu su AMiq quJY koaU swQ n dY hY ] Awn kI bwq clwq ho kwhy kau sMig kI dyh n sMig isDY hY ]160]
transliteration: Bhaoun Bhandaar Sabhai Bar Naar(u) Su Ant(i) Tujhai Ko( i)  Saath Na Dai Hai|| Aan Kibaat Chalaat Ho Kaahe Kau San(i) Kideh Na San(i) Sidhai Hai||160||
translation: “Your treasures and your beautiful women, none of them will accompany you at the end; leave all others, even your own body will not accompany you.”160.
